# Copy to web/.env.local. See docs/deploy.md for the full env-var checklist.

# --- Public (exposed to the browser) ---
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# --- Server-only ---
DATABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET=

# --- AI / quality vectors (Quality Fix override) ---
# Server-only. NEVER prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_ — these never reach the browser.
# Wire via `vercel env add <NAME> <env> --value '<value>' --yes` for
# production + development; pass an empty positional git-branch arg for preview:
# `vercel env add <NAME> preview "" --value '<value>' --yes`.
#
# Costs are governed by aiGuard against AI_MONTHLY_BUDGET_USD_PER_CHILD.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=               # Claude Sonnet 4.6 — vocab suggestions, symbol-image audit, sentence completion
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=              # ElevenLabs Multilingual v2 — TTS for both EN + AR
# OPENAI_API_KEY=                  # Whisper STT (whisper-1)

# --- Cost guard ---
# Quality Fix raised this from 5 → 20 to fund ElevenLabs + Claude + Whisper
# at expected per-child volume. Cache hit rate ≥ 60% keeps the line item low.
AI_MONTHLY_BUDGET_USD_PER_CHILD=20

# --- Observability (Module 9) ---
# SENTRY_DSN=
# POSTHOG_PROJECT_API_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# Module 2.A.1.bypass — Auth bypass mode
#
# DEVELOPMENT ONLY. NEVER set in production after launch.
#
# When AUTH_BYPASS_USER_ID is set, every visitor is auto-signed-in as
# the matching test caregiver — no email handshake, no real signup. This
# unblocks the Modules 6-9 buildout while keeping every page testable in
# a real browser. RLS stays fully enforced; we are skipping the human
# auth step, NOT the database security model.
#
# To enable:
#   1. pnpm exec tsx db/scripts/seed-dev-caregiver.ts
#   2. Copy the printed UUID into AUTH_BYPASS_USER_ID below.
#   3. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_BYPASS=1 (boolean flag — never the user ID).
#
# To DISABLE before market launch:
#   1. Remove AUTH_BYPASS_USER_ID + NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_BYPASS from every
#      Vercel env scope (production, preview, development).
#   2. Force-redeploy.
#   3. Verify /api/health/auth reports bypassActive:false.
#   4. Run db/scripts/delete-dev-caregiver.ts to wipe the test caregiver
#      and all associated test data (cascade).
#   5. Real signup flow works on its own.
#
# next.config.mjs has a build-time guard that REFUSES to ship a production
# Vercel build if AUTH_BYPASS_USER_ID is set without an explicit
# ALLOW_AUTH_BYPASS_IN_PRODUCTION=true override.
# =============================================================================
# AUTH_BYPASS_USER_ID=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_BYPASS=
# ALLOW_AUTH_BYPASS_IN_PRODUCTION=true
